Laggie.. <br>
<br>
The only people left are not just Reserves.  There are hundreds of Acitive duty folk in the US, as well as Reservists (one being myself and a former Gulf War Vet) and Guard folk as well.<br>
<br>
If you have noticed, there are Active duty folk in Iraq/Kuwait, but there are also Reservists and Guards there too.  If something was to happen in Korea, we already have Active duty folk there, and there are Reserve and Guard bases that have personnel ready to deploy there too (that being their part of the world to watch).  Take into account there are Army/Navy/Air Force and Marines that make up our Military might, both active and reserve/guard.<br>
<br>
I appreciate the concern for our country and our men/women in uniform.  While it looks like the world might be coming to a head with all this conflict, it is just a drop in the bucket when you look back in the history of conflicts. <br>
<br>
Will it be over in 2 weeks?  I doubt it.  But you can believe that most of the uniformed services don't look at the short picture.  News crews always look at the bleak part and the short term.  WW2 took years but you didn't hear the news folk complaining that it was taking 'too long' then (dictator, but a different name)(shrug).<br>
<br>
Just my 2 coppers.<br>
