<br>
This is a common misconception that the press would like you to believe that we could have actually accomplished.  This is something that could have never happened at that time.  Why?<br>
<br>
Well, as you know the UN Resolution at the time when Desert Storm came about prohibited the coalition forces from entering Iraq.  I'm sure that we could have accomplished such a mission at that time if we acted unilaterally or with a different composition of forces, but we were not allowed to do so.  Geroge Bush (41) followed the UN resolution and international law that bound the actions of the coalition forces to the soul purpose of removing the Iraqi forces from Kuwait.<br>
<br>
Remember, one of the major differences between the current coalition and the previous one is that there are NO ARAB forces in this coalition.  We may have some backing verbally, monitarily, or willing to help with the reconstruction of Iraq, but there is NO military involvement.<br>
<br>
This will not be an easy conquest.  I think that the press has done this country a disservice by portraying this war as  they have done.  Fox News and other 'conservative' sources seem to paint a more realistic picture of the war.  Jeraldo, Arnette, and any other press agent that jeapordizes the lives of any soldier should simply be left behind in the desert to make their own way back to the land that they take so much for granted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/btheprogenysentinels47001.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pishthunderpaw>pish thunderpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Destroyerkitty</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(4/2/03 7:28:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ftheprogenysentinels47001frm52.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: OMG!!!!!</span><hr size=1> hey all,<br>
